    "recap_headline": "Lehigh University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "BETHLEHEM, Pa. \u2013 In its final tune-up before Patriot League play begins this weekend, Lehigh fell to Saint Peter's 12-3 Wednesday at J. David Walker Field.\nSenior\nTrystan Crawford\npaced the offense with two hits, but an early 5-0 deficit was too much to overcome.\nA Bobby Lavely three-run home run to right put the Peacocks up 5-0 in the top of the third inning.\nLehigh pulled a run back on a sacrifice fly off the bat of first-year\nMax Dantoni\n, that scored first-year\nSilvio Giardina\nin the bottom of the third.\nSophomore\nIan Wirtz\ntripled home Crawford in the fourth and then scored when junior\nRobbie Carvelli\nreached on an error to bring Lehigh within 6-3.\nSaint Peter's added two runs in the fifth, sixth and ninth innings to account for the final margin.\nFirst-year\nRyan Holman\nstarted on the mound and was charged with five runs over 2.2 innings. He walked two and struck out four. First-year\nDeclan Wilkes\nretired all six batters he faced over two scoreless innings.\nLehigh mustered six hits on the afternoon and was hurt by three errors in the field.\nLuke Schwartz joined Lavely with three RBIs for Saint Peter's.\nThe Mountain Hawks open Patriot League play at home this weekend with a three-game series against Navy, beginning with a contest Friday at 3 p.m."
  },
